{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\">You are Pixel P.I., a hacker detective who has to solve old cases to find clues about her own past. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">After an unknown incident Pixel lost her memories, and the only link to her past is a list of old cases that she found. What's wrong with these cases? Why were they never solved? And what kind of clues do they contain about Pixel's past? These are all mysteries that <strong>you</strong> will need to solve in order to help Pixel.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">These cases will force you to reason, to make deductions, and ultimately to give them resolution. You will have to explain your reasoning to your companion, to make sure you are not making any mistake and driving the investigation to the wrong place. They will keep you grounded, and let you know if your logic is faulty, because in this game <strong>you</strong> will write the deductions.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">The Game Features 6 Cases</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> The axe murderer</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">The broken case</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">????</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">????</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">????</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">The final case</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Each case features a new set of characters that you can interact with.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Game Mechanics</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> Interrogation: You can get clues and information about the case by asking your own questions to suspects and witnesses.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> Contradict: Show a clue and explain why it shows that the person is lying to force them to correct their statement.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> Accuse suspect: Solve the case by presenting all your clues against someone.</p></li></ul>","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2448910/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1739308424","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2448910/page.bg.jpg?t=1739308424","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2448910/248ac01ce4a7d272e67795570c9d01b8592dc797/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1739308424","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2448910/248ac01ce4a7d272e67795570c9d01b8592dc797/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1739308424","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Steam Achievements","id":22},{"description":"Captions available","id":13}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"detailed_description":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\">You are Pixel P.I., a hacker detective who has to solve old cases to find clues about her own past. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">After an unknown incident Pixel lost her memories, and the only link to her past is a list of old cases that she found. What's wrong with these cases? Why were they never solved? And what kind of clues do they contain about Pixel's past? These are all mysteries that <strong>you</strong> will need to solve in order to help Pixel.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">These cases will force you to reason, to make deductions, and ultimately to give them resolution. You will have to explain your reasoning to your companion, to make sure you are not making any mistake and driving the investigation to the wrong place. They will keep you grounded, and let you know if your logic is faulty, because in this game <strong>you</strong> will write the deductions.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">The Game Features 6 Cases</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"